  "body": "\r\n***Type***: Bug \r\n***Summary***: On iPad Pro the bottom tab bar is covered by the safe area, meaning the black bar overlaps the text labels. And when the panel is minimized - the device bar overlaps icons.\r\nWe need to have extra padding, just like we do for the iPhone X.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nStatus app bottom tab panel (Chats-Dapps-Wallet-Profile) is not overlapped by iPad Pro's bottom bar\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nOn iPad Pro the bottom tab bar is covered by the safe area, meaning the black bar overlaps the text labels.\r\n\r\n![image1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/59178887-fe405780-8b68-11e9-8701-734c9a7abebf.jpeg)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on iPad Pro\r\n- Navigate between screens\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: Release 0.13.0/ Develop\r\n- Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n",
